@page "/admin/tour-scan"

<PageTitle>HIP Tour Scan</PageTitle>

<section class="hip-tour-backdrop">
    <div class="hip-tour-card">
        <button type="button" aria-label="Close">x</button>
        <h1>Sample Threat — Detected</h1>
        <p>This is what HIP catches before it reaches users.</p>
        <article class="hip-message-sample">
            <strong>unknown_9821 · Telegram</strong>
            <span>"You won a prize! Claim it now: htt ps://bit.ly/win-now"</span>
        </article>
        <article class="hip-danger-box">
            <h2>HIP blocked this message <span class="hip-pill danger">Dangerous</span></h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Broken-up URL to avoid scanners</li>
                <li>Domain resolves to scam-prize.xyz, a known phishing domain</li>
                <li>New account created 2 days ago</li>
                <li>No verified identity signature</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
        <p>HIP never read private message text to make this decision. It analyzed URL structure, sender history, and domain reputation.</p>
        <div class="hip-button-row">
            <a href="/">Back to tour</a>
            <a class="primary-button" href="/">Start using HIP</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
